<TITLE> Verdict on Loby case set for July 5 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 01 (bdnews24.com) - The verdict in the tax-dodging case against former BNP MP Ali Asgar Loby will be handed down on July 5. The date was announced Sunday by Judge Shahed Noor Uddin of special judge's court - 3. The same court will hear a case on July 2 that was filed by the Anticorruption Commission against Loby and wife Khasnud Asgar. ACC deputy director Shirin Parvin filed the case with Gulshan police station on March 21 on charges of earning money through unfair means. Deputy tax commissioner of the National Board of Revenue, Nurul Amin, filed the tax-dodging case with Dhaka Metropolitan Senior Special Judge's Court on May 23. Loby stands accused of withholding approximately Tk 4.5 crore in unpaid taxes. The charges were framed against Loby in the case on June 5. bdnews
